	<title>Will Smith on Adolf Hitler</title>

	<category term="Eugenics" />
	<category term="History" />
	<category term="Politics" />

	<content type="xhtml">
		<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
			<div class="quote">
				<blockquote cite="http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20168278,00.html">
					<p>
						Adolf Hitler was a vile, heinous, vicious killer responsible for one of the greatest acts of evil committed on this planet. [&#8230; but &#8230;] Even Hitler didn&#8217;t wake up going, &#8220;Let me do the most evil thing I can do today.&#8221; I think he woke up in the morning and using a twisted, backwards logic, he set out to do what he thought was &#8220;good&#8221;.
					</p>
				</blockquote>
				<p class="quote-by">
					-- Willard Christopher Smith, Jr.
				</p>
				<p class="quote-from">
					from "<a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20168278,00.html">Will Smith Explains Hitler Quote</a>"
